<h4 id="h">H</h4>
<p>Duality between Polar and Pole</p>

<p><img src="/images/space-hyperbolic-geometry-polarity.gif" /></p>

<h4 id="theorem-polar-independence-theorem">Theorem: Polar Independence Theorem</h4>
<p>The polar does not depend on the choice of lines through a.</p>
<h4 id="theorem-pole-of-a-line-theorem">Theorem: Pole of A Line Theorem</h4>
<p>Every line A which is not a diameter of a circle, is the polar of a unique point a, called the pole
of A.</p>

<h4 id="polarity-holds-for-general-conics">Polarity holds for general conics</h4>

